            <div class="cardio-types">
                <h2>Types of Cardio Classes</h2>
                <p>At FIT-TRACK, we offer various cardio styles to cater to different needs and preferences:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>HIIT:</strong> High-Intensity Interval Training for maximum calorie burn.</li>
                    <li><strong>Spin:</strong> Indoor cycling classes for a great leg workout.</li>
                    <li><strong>Running:</strong> Group runs for all levels, from beginners to advanced.</li>
                    <li><strong>Aerobics:</strong> Fun dance-based workouts to get your heart pumping.</li>
                    <li><strong>Kickboxing:</strong> A high-energy workout combining martial arts and cardio.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="cardio-benefits">
                <h2>Benefits of Cardio</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Improves cardiovascular health</li>
                    <li>Burns calories and aids in weight loss</li>
                    <li>Boosts mood and reduces stress</li>
                    <li>Enhances endurance and stamina</li>
                    <li>Improves sleep quality</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            < class="cardio-exercises">
                <h2>Basic Cardio Exercises</h2>
                
                <div class="cardio-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/CARDIO/jumping jack.jpg" alt="Jumping Jacks">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>1. Jumping Jacks</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Stand with your feet together and arms at your sides.<br>
                            2. Jump up, spreading your legs and raising your arms overhead.<br>
                            3. Jump back to the starting position and repeat.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Great full-body workout that increases heart rate.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="cardio-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/CARDIO/burpees.jpeg" alt="Burpees">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>2. Burpees</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Start in a standing position.<br>
                            2. Drop into a squat and place your hands on the ground.<br>
                            3. Kick your feet back into a plank position.<br>
                            4. Return to squat and jump up explosively.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Full-body exercise that builds strength and endurance.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Existing cardio exercises -->
                <div class="cardio-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/CARDIO/jump rope.jpg" alt="Jump Rope">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>3. Jump Rope</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Hold the handles of a jump rope and stand with feet hip-width apart.<br>
                            Swing the rope overhead and jump as it passes under your feet.<br>
                            Land lightly on your toes and keep a slight bend in your knees.<br>
                            Repeat for several minutes.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Improves cardiovascular endurance, burns calories, strengthens legs and calves.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="cardio-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/CARDIO/high knees.jpg" alt="High Knees">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>4. High Knees</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Stand tall and lift one knee toward your chest.<br>
                            Quickly switch to the other knee, moving in a running motion.<br>
                            Keep your arms pumping and core engaged.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Boosts heart rate, improves coordination, strengthens legs and core.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="cardio-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/CARDIO/butt kicks.jpeg" alt="Butt Kicks">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>5. Butt Kicks</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Stand with feet hip-width apart.<br>
                            Jog in place, kicking your heels up toward your glutes.<br>
                            Engage your core and keep an upright posture.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens hamstrings, improves cardiovascular health, increases agility.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                
                
